The paper deals with the detection of anomalous activities in cryptocurrency markets, which is a common problem in the field of computer security (cs.CR). The proposed method involves the use of distance and density metrics, which are commonly used in machine learning and data analysis (cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.DS). The paper also involves the use of automatic threshold setting, which is a common problem in information retrieval (cs.IR).
